        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 12:17PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 1216 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Meridian State Park, or 14 miles northwest of Clifton, moving
southeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Meridian and Meridian State Park around 1220 PM CDT.
Clifton around 1230 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Pancake, Walnut
Springs, Cayote, Eulogy, Kopperl, Olin, Brazos Point, Cedar Shores,
Whiteway, and Levita.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
